data.title: Frank Archibald MacDougall
data.meta_description: Frank Archibald MacDougall was a Canadian pioneering forest ranger in Ontario, Canada. Known as the "flying Superintendent of Algonquin Park", he was important in the development of the park system in the province and for the use of airplanes in forestry.
data.text:
Frank Archibald MacDougall (16 June 1896 â€“ 27 June 1975) was a Canadian pioneering forest ranger in Ontario, Canada. Known as the "flying Superintendent of Algonquin Park", he was important in the development of the park system in the province and for the use of airplanes in forestry.[1]
